HEADWORD: Bodhisattwa
<hw>Bo`dhi*satt"wa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Skr. <ets>b⟦omac⟧dhisattva</ets> (perh. through Pali
<ets>b⟦omac⟧dhisatt⟦omac⟧</ets>); fr. <ets>b⟦omac⟧dhi</ets> knowledge,
enlightenment + <ets>sattva</ets> being, essence.]</ety>
<fld>(Buddhism)</fld> <def>One who has reached the highest degree of
saintship, so that in his next incarnation he will be a Buddha, or
savior of the world.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Bo"dhi*sat`ship</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
